text.tspan: Imagine a nice evening at home in the wintertime. Outside
cold and dark, inside cozy and light. Lamps and lumi-
naires are an important and emotional part of your home.
However, even if they are already much more efficient,
they consume energy. Especially when the entire house is
illuminated even if certain rooms are empty. Occupa-
tion-based lighting can avoid this and help to save signifi-
cant amounts of energy: Radar sensors use presence
detection to make sure that lights are only on when a
XENSIV™ 60 GHz radar sensors could reduce energy con
sumption by 5%, resulting in potential savings
of around 2.15 TWh for the EU residential sector
